ding-v3", "object": "list", "usage": {"prompt_tokens": 1144, "total_tokens": 1144}, "id": "c8c078ec-d184-9f01-beba-ec1c05137c97"}, "input": {"input": ["重铠:The heavy armor worn by the approaching warrior, resembling an ancient figure", "战马:战马是蛮族骑兵的坐骑，高大且强壮。这些战马被骑乘着接近的战士们驾驭，在寒冷的天气中呼出白色的气息。战马不仅体型健硕，还展现出强大的力量和耐力，适合在战场上冲锋陷阵。", "乌黑的幡:The black banner carried by the lead rider, with cold silver light flowing on it", "山碧空:山碧空 is a mysterious and enigmatic figure who plays a pivotal role in the narrative, embodying a complex blend of power, mysticism, and diplomacy. He is described as an elderly man, tall and lean, with silver hair, often seen wearing a black cloak and carrying a ceramic vessel. His appearance and demeanor exude an air of authority and otherworldliness.\n\n山碧空 claims to possess extraordinary powers, including the ability to revive the dead, control natural phenomena, and manipulate illusions. He is said to be a master of the \"密罗心幻之术\" (Miro Heart Illusion Technique), capable of paralyzing the senses and creating powerful illusions. These abilities are demonstrated to both the Great Khan and the Great Shaman, as he seeks to prove his capabilities and gain their trust. However, his trustworthiness is occasionally questioned by the Great Khan and his advisors, adding an element of skepticism to his claims.\n\n山碧空 is deeply connected to the Bai Imperial Family, to whom he pledges his loyalty. He claims to serve under the stars and carries a great mission from the Eastern Continent. As a secret envoy of the Great Emperor of the Eastern Continent, he is tasked with forming an alliance with the Qingyang Tribe to address future threats. He presents himself as a diplomatic envoy, delivering imperial edicts and advocating for unity between the Eastern Empire and the Qingyang Tribe.\n\nIn addition to his diplomatic and mystical roles, 山碧空 is a healer. He is the primary figure responsible for saving the life of the Great Lord's son, A'Su, leading a ritual to heal him. He is also involved in conducting ceremonies, such as the singing ritual, and handling the remains of the deceased.\n\n山碧空's identity is further shrouded in mystery as he claims to be the \"Lord of the World\" and appears in the hallucinations of the Great Shaman. He is portrayed as a messenger of the celestial gods, possessing the ability to predict the future and persuade others to accept his prophecies.\n\nIn summary, 山碧空 is a multifaceted character who combines the roles of a healer, diplomat, and mystic. His extraordinary powers, loyalty to the Bai Imperial Family, and mission to forge alliances make him a key figure in the story, though his true intentions and the extent of his powers remain subjects of intrigue and speculation.", "皇帝:皇帝是东陆的统治者，通过山碧空传递亲笔书信，展示其权威", "海峡:海峡是分隔东陆和蛮族地区的自然屏障，同时也是信使越过的地方，用于传递东陆天启城胤朝大皇帝的亲笔书信。作为连接两地的关键通道，海峡在信息传递和区域分隔中扮演着重要角色。", "皇帝之信:皇帝之信是皇帝通过山碧空传递的亲笔书信，以黄金制成，象征权威", "信使:信使是传递皇帝书信的人，越过海峡将书信送达", "大火堆:大火堆是蛮族接待贵宾的重要场所，同时也是山碧空与大君、大合萨会面的地点。在这个场所，山碧空曾坐下与蛮族的领袖们进行会晤，体现了大火堆在蛮族社会中的重要地位和仪式性功能。", "风炎皇帝:风炎皇帝是东陆历史上的一位重要统治者，其统治时期与当前形势有所不同。他是五十多年前震惊蛮族的皇帝，曾多次与北陆敌对，并发动了两次大规模的北伐入侵，导致蛮族大量伤亡。在早春四月，他撤离了朔方原，这一行动进一步加剧了与北陆的紧张关系。风炎皇帝曾与大君的父亲进行过两次决战，并在铁线一战中使蛮族损失惨重，成为蛮族历史上的重要敌人。\n\n此外，风炎皇帝在四十年前颁布了《七海税兵制》，这一制度影响深远，被洛子鄢称赞为英雄之举。他还曾写信给钦达翰王招降，其印章被用于这些信件中，显示了他试图通过外交手段解决与北陆的冲突。风炎皇帝作为东陆的统治者，不仅在军事上表现出色，还在政治和经济上留下了深刻的印记，成为东陆历史上不可忽视的重要人物。"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}